node.text: Just a few hours before the @paralympics Closing Ceremony we catch up with @birgitskarstein - a para-athlete from Norway 🇳🇴 . She competed at Sochi, Rio, PyeongChang, and now at the Tokyo 2020 Paralympic Games, where she won a gold medal. Birgit tells us why the Paralympics are so important and how she is spending her time after the Games.

⁠⁠
Ahead of Emma Raducanu and Leylah Fernandez's all-teenager showdown at this year's tournament, enjoy these vintage snaps from '99! 😍⁠⁠
⁠⁠

node.text:
These young tennis stars are making history at the #USOpen!

Great Britain's Emma Raducanu, 18, and Canada's Leylah Fernandez, 19, have both reached this year's final at Flushing Meadows, setting up the first all-teenager grand slam final since Serena Williams v Martina Hingis at the 1999 US Open.

We can't wait to see what they serve up in Saturday's decider. 🤩
